= Welcome to the Polypaudio Trac! =

Polypaudio is a sound server for Unix/Linux, see http://0pointer.de/lennart/projects/polypaudio/ for more information.

The following polypaudio drivers are currrently available for other software:

 * [http://0pointer.de/lennart/projects/libao-polyp libao] (older version merged in libao's SVN)
 * [http://0pointer.de/lennart/projects/gst-polyp GStreamer] (older version merged in gst's CVS)
 * [http://0pointer.de/lennart/projects/xmms-polyp XMMS]

Available for 0.7.0, need updating for 0.9.0:
 * The current MPlayer CVS contains a driver for polypaudio
 * PortAudio patches are in the works
 * Miguel Freitas wrote a Polypaudio driver for Xine. (already merged in Xine's CVS)

If you want to be notified when a new SVN commit is made, consider subscribing to the Timeline RSS feed.

Have a loook on the current SVN sources of Polypaudio in source:/trunk

